description._content: Description: At this point it was necessary to get from the crest in the foreground across the wadi (deeper than it looks) on to the edge marked X-Y. Location: Jebel Tubaik, Turkey Date: 1890-1899 Description: Solving the problem at D. The route has been reconnoitred & cleared of the worst stones. Maj Goodwin (on foot) leading the cars. Location: Jebel Tubaik, Turkey Date: 1890-1899 Description: Building up a track across a rocky ridge. Location: Jebel Tubaik, Turkey Date: 1890-1899 Description: Typical of the loose rocky formation of the Jebel Tubaik. Location: Jebel Tubaik, Turkey Date: 1890-1899 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/672 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
